  "bench_knowledge": [
    "Proteins in 50% glycerol stocks (enzymes, antibodies, recombinant carriers) stay liquid at \u221220\u00b0C but denature rapidly above ~4\u00b0C. The glycerol stock is viscous, requiring reverse pipetting to eliminate air bubbles. Vortexing creates a high-shear air\u2013water interface that unfolds proteins.",
    "Proteins, oligonucleotides, and antibodies at low concentrations lose significant material to non-specific adsorption onto standard polypropylene and polystyrene surfaces within 30\u201360 minutes, particularly below 100 \u00b5g/mL. LoBind surfaces have reduced hydrophobic character; adding BSA or another carrier protein competes for adsorption sites and stabilises the stock at very low concentrations."
  ],
